description: Goa Jomblang merupakan gua vertikal yang bertipe collapse doline. Gua ini terbentuk akibat proses geologi amblasnya tanah beserta vegetasi yang ada di atasnya ke dasar bumi yang terjadi ribuan tahun lalu. Runtuhan ini membentuk sinkhole atau sumuran yang dalam bahasa Jawa dikenal dengan istilah luweng. Saat ini Gua Jomblang merupakan tempat konservasi tumbuhan purba dan dikembangkan menjadi tempat wisata minat khusus yang mana dikelola oleh penduduk atau warga setempat. Untuk menuruni gua vertikal ini pihak pengelola sudah menyediakan perlengkapan lengkap sesuai standar keselamatan caving di gua vertikal. Sinar matahari yang menerobos masuk dari Luweng Grubug setinggi 90 meter membentuk satu tiang cahaya, menyinari flowstone yang indah serta kedalaman gua yang gelap gulita. Air yang menetes dari ketinggian turut mempercantik pemandangan. Tidak salah jika banyak orang terkagum-kagum datang ke sini ketika menyaksikan lukisan alam yang dikenal dengan istilah "cahaya surga".
trans_desc: Jomblang Goa is a vertical cave that type Collapse Doline.This cave was formed due to the geological process of the collapse of the soil and vegetation on it to the bottom of the earth that occurred thousands of years ago.This collapse forms a sinkhole or a well that is known as Luweng.At present the Jomblang Cave is a conservation place for ancient plants and is developed into a special interest tourist spot which is managed by residents or local residents.To go down this vertical cave the manager has provided complete equipment according to the safety standard of caving in the vertical cave.The sunlight that broke into the Grubug Luweng as high as 90 meters to form a pole of light, illuminating beautiful flowstone and the depth of the pitch black cave.Water that drips from a height also enhances the view.It is not wrong if many people are amazed to come here when watching a natural painting known as "Light of Heaven".
combined: Natural Jomblang Goa is a vertical cave that type Collapse Doline.This cave was formed due to the geological process of the collapse of the soil and vegetation on it to the bottom of the earth that occurred thousands of years ago.This collapse forms a sinkhole or a well that is known as Luweng.At present the Jomblang Cave is a conservation place for ancient plants and is developed into a special interest tourist spot which is managed by residents or local residents.To go down this vertical cave the manager has provided complete equipment according to the safety standard of caving in the vertical cave.The sunlight that broke into the Grubug Luweng as high as 90 meters to form a pole of light, illuminating beautiful flowstone and the depth of the pitch black cave.Water that drips from a height also enhances the view.It is not wrong if many people are amazed to come here when watching a natural painting known as "Light of Heaven".

description: Di Gunung Ireng Srumbung Teman Brisik bisa menemukan spot fajar terbaik tanpa harus mendaki gunung berhari-hari. Dari sini, kita juga disuguhkan pemandangan bak negeri di atas awan. Barisan kabut yang menyelimuti area puncak bukit membuat kita serasa berdiri di atas awan. Tempat ini sangat fotogenik dan tempat yang nyaman buat refreshing. Mulai dari spot rumah kecil, gazebo sampai gardu pandang membuat Teman Brisik dengan leluasa memotret momen matahari terbit dari berbagai spot yang telah disediakan.
trans_desc: On Mount Ireng Srumbung Brisa friends can find the best dawn spots without having to climb a mountain for days.From here, we are also presented with views like a country above the clouds.The fog line that enveloped the hilltop area made us feel like standing on the clouds.This place is very photogenic and a comfortable place for refreshing.Starting from the small house spot, gazebo to the viewing post made friends brisik freely photograph the moment of the sunrise from the various spots that have been provided.

description: Pantai Samas merupakan salah satu pantai yang berada di deretan pantai sebelah timur Pantai Parangtritis. Lokasi Pantai Samas kurang lebih 14 km arah selatan Kota Bantul atau sekitar 35 km dari pusat Kota Yogyakarta, tepatnya di Desa Srigading, Kecamatan Sanden, Kabupaten Bantul, Yogyakarta. Pantai Samas terkenal dengan deburan ombaknya yang menggulung, angin lautnya yang kencang dan sebagai tempat persinggahan penyu-penyu langka seperti penyu sisik dan penyu hijau untuk bertelur. Selain itu, kawasan Pantai Samas juga memiliki delta-delta sungai dan danau air tawar yang membentuk telaga. Akan tetapi Pantai Samas memiliki bibir pantai ang agak curam sehingga berbahaya dan tidak disarankan untuk mandi di pantai.
trans_desc: Samas Beach is one of the beaches located in the row of beaches east of Parangtritis Beach.The location of Samas Beach is approximately 14 km south of Bantul City or about 35 km from the center of Yogyakarta City, precisely in Srigading Village, Sanden District, Bantul Regency, Yogyakarta.Samas Beach is famous for its rolling waves, the sea breeze is strong and as a place for rare turtles such as turtles scales and green turtles to lay eggs.In addition, the Samas Beach area also has a Delta-Delta River and Freshwater Lake that forms a lake.However, Samas Beach has a rather steep beach so it is dangerous and is not recommended to take a bath on the beach.
combined: Nature, beach Samas Beach is one of the beaches located in the row of beaches east of Parangtritis Beach.The location of Samas Beach is approximately 14 km south of Bantul City or about 35 km from the center of Yogyakarta City, precisely in Srigading Village, Sanden District, Bantul Regency, Yogyakarta.Samas Beach is famous for its rolling waves, the sea breeze is strong and as a place for rare turtles such as turtles scales and green turtles to lay eggs.In addition, the Samas Beach area also has a Delta-Delta River and Freshwater Lake that forms a lake.However, Samas Beach has a rather steep beach so it is dangerous and is not recommended to take a bath on the beach.

description: Pantai Siung berlokasi di Gunung Kidul, Yogyakarta. Pantai ini  spesial karena lanskapnya yang dikelilingi oleh tebing-tebing tinggi. Karena keunikan itulah, pemerintah Jogja meresmikan Pantai Siung sebagai lokasi panjat tebing. Selama di Pantai Siung, kamu akan melihat banyak batu karang raksasa tersebar di sebelah barat dan timur pantai. Selain menjadi ciri khas Pantai Siung, keberadaan batu karang ternyata membawa makna bagi asal-usul nama pantai ini. Sebagai rangkuman, di pantai ini kalian dapat melakukan aktivitas panjat tebing, hammocking, berkemah, dan jalan-jalan di bukit pengilon.
trans_desc: Siung Beach is located in Gunung Kidul, Yogyakarta.This beach is special because the landscape is surrounded by high cliffs.Because of that uniqueness, the Jogja government inaugurated Siung Beach as a rock climbing location.While at Siung Beach, you will see a lot of giant rocks scattered to the west and east of the beach.Besides being a characteristic of Siung Beach, the existence of rocks turns out to bring meaning to the origin of the name of this beach.As a summary, on this beach you can do rock climbing activities, hammocking, camping, and walking on the Bukit Pengilon.

description: Goa yang berada di kawasan Pegunungan Menoreh ini merupakan goa basah, alias terdapat aliran air di dalamnya. Goa tersebut tepatnya berada di Desa Donorejo, Kecamatan Kaligesing, Kabupaten Purworejo, Jawa Tengah, berbatasan langsung dengan Kulonprogo di Yogyakarta. Goa ini memiliki panjang + 700 meter dengan cabang-cabang goa sekitar 150 – 300 meter dan berdiameter 15 meter. Sehingga untuk masuk ke dalam goa, pengunjung harus menyusuri anak tangga menurun yang cukup melalahkan. Yang mana rasa lelah itu akan segera hilang begitu mulai memasuki mulut goa. Sebab dari mulut goa itu saja keindahan ukiran batu di dalam goa sudah terlihat jelas.
trans_desc: Goa in the Menoreh mountainous area is a wet cave, aka there is a flow of water in it.The cave is precisely located in Donorejo Village, Kaligesing District, Purworejo Regency, Central Java, directly adjacent to Kulonprogo in Yogyakarta.This cave has a length of + 700 meters with cave branches around 150-300 meters and 15 meters in diameter.So as to enter the cave, visitors must walk along the decreased steps that are quite blaming.Which fatigue will soon disappear when it starts to enter the mouth of the cave.Because from the mouth of the cave, the beauty of the stone carvings in the cave is clearly visible.

description: Candi Sari juga disebut Candi Bendah adalah candi Buddha yang berada tidak jauh dari Candi Sambi Sari, Candi Kalasan dan Candi Prambanan, yaitu di bagian sebelah timur laut dari kota Yogyakarta, dan tidak begitu jauh dari Bandara Adisucipto. Candi ini dibangun pada sekitar abad ke-8 dan ke-9 pada saat zaman Kerajaan Mataram Kuno dengan bentuk yang sangat indah. Pada bagian atas candi ini terdapat 9 buah stupa seperti yang tampak pada stupa di Candi Borobudur, dan tersusun dalam 3 deretan sejajar. Bentuk bangunan candi serta ukiran relief yang ada pada dinding candi sangat mirip dengan relief di Candi Plaosan. Beberapa ruangan bertingkat dua berada persis di bawah masing-masing stupa, dan diperkirakan dipakai untuk tempat meditasi bagi para pendeta Buddha (biksu) pada zaman dahulunya. Candi Sari pada masa lampau merupakan suatu Vihara Buddha, dan dipakai sebagai tempat belajar dan berguru bagi para biksu. Selain untuk wisata Budaya dan Sejarah, pengunjung juga dapat bersepeda. Bersepeda di candi ini tidak akan memakan banyak waktu dikarenakan candi yang berukuran kecil. Selain di sekitar candi, para pengunjung juga dapat bersepeda menyusuri candi-candi lainnya yang lokasinya berdekatan. Para pengunjung dapat bercengkarama dengan penduduk sekitar candi untuk memperkaya cerita dan budaya dengan dalam dari Candi Sari ini sendiri.
trans_desc: Sari Temple is also called Brenda Temple is a Buddhist temple which is located not far from Sambi Sari Temple, Kalasan Temple and Prambanan Temple, namely in the northeast of Yogyakarta, and not so far from Adisucipto Airport.This temple was built around the 8th and 9th centuries during the era of the Ancient Mataram kingdom with a very beautiful form.At the top of this temple there are 9 stupas as shown in the stupa in Borobudur Temple, and arranged in 3 rows of parallel.The shape of the temple building and relief engraving on the walls of the temple is very similar to the reliefs in the Plaosan temple.Some two-story rooms are exactly below each stupor, and are expected to be used for meditation for Buddhist priests (monks) in the past.Sari Temple in the past was a Buddhist temple, and was used as a place to learn and study for monks.In addition to cultural and historical tourism, visitors can also cycling.Cycling in this temple will not take much time due to a small temple.Besides around the temple, visitors can also cycling along other temples which are located close together.The visitors can fight with residents around the temple to enrich the story and culture in the Sari Temple itself.

description: Desa Wisata Pentingsari terletak di lereng Gunung Merapi, sekitar 22,5 kilometer dari pusat Kota Yogyakarta. Desa ini dikenal di mancanegara sebagai salah satu desa wisata dengan segudang penghargaan. Dusun Pentingsari berbentuk seperti semenanjung dimana sebelah barat terdapat lembah yang sangat curam yaitu kali Kuning dan sebelah selatan terdapat lebah yang berupak Goa Ledok / Ponteng dan Gondoran sebelah timur terdapat lembah yang curam yaitu Kali Pawon dan sebelah utara merupakan dataran yang dapat berhubungan langsung dengan tanah di sekeliling kelurahan Umbulharjo sampai ke pelataran gunung Merapi. Dusun Pentingsari terdiri dari dua dusun yaitu Bonorejo dan Pentingsari. Ada beberapa program wisata desa, seperti live in, kemah, trekking, atau outbound yang bisa dinikmati. Untuk kegiatan wisata budaya, wisatawan bisa mengikuti kegiatan, seperti belajar gamelan, menari, membatik, membuat wayang rumput, dan membuat janur.
trans_desc: Tourism Village is important is located on the slopes of Mount Merapi, about 22.5 kilometers from the center of Yogyakarta.This village is known in foreign countries as one of the tourist villages with a myriad of awards.The important hamlet is shaped like a peninsula where the west there is a very steep valley, namely Kali Kuning and the south there are bees with Ledok / Ponteng caves and the east gondoran there is a steep valley, namely the pawon river and the north is a plain that can be directly related to the land inAround Umbulharjo Village, to the courtyard of Mount Merapi.The important hamlet consists of two hamlets, namely Bonorejo and MataSari.There are several village tourism programs, such as live in, camp, trekking, or outbound that can be enjoyed.For cultural tourism activities, tourists can participate in activities, such as learning gamelan, dancing, making batik, making grass puppets, and making fan.

description: Kawasan Ekosistem Gunung Purba Nglanggeran atau yang biasa disebut Gunung Nglanggeran ini merupakan kawasan yang litologinya disusun oleh material vulkanik tua, berbentuk gunung batu raksasa yang membentang sepanjang kurang lebih 800 meter dengan tinggi mencapai 300 meter. Gunung Nglanggeran dinyatakan sebagai gunung api purba dari hasil penelitian dan refrensi yang ada. Sekitar 60-70 juta tahun yang lalu Gunung tersebut merupakan gunung berapi aktif.
trans_desc: The Nglanggeran Ancient Mountain Ecosystem area or commonly called Mount Nglanggeran is an area whose lithology is composed of old volcanic material, shaped like a giant stone mountain that stretches for approximately 800 meters with a height of 300 meters.Nglanggeran Mountain is declared an ancient volcano from the results of existing research and references.About 60-70 million years ago the mountain was an active volcano.
